Gate 4: Physical Grounding (Breath & Hold)
Objective: Activate the parasympathetic nervous system and transition the brain from high-beta (panic/craving) to alpha (calm/focus) waves.
Psychological Basis:
Controlled breathing is one of the fastest ways to shift the autonomic nervous system from sympathetic (fight-or-flight) to parasympathetic (rest-and-digest). The 4-7-8 breathing technique (inhale 4s, hold 7s, exhale 8s) is clinically proven to reduce anxiety and cravings.
Why This Works for Addiction:
Cravings trigger physical symptoms: rapid heart rate, shallow breathing, tension
Controlled breathing directly counteracts these symptoms
The "hold" requirement prevents the user from closing the app
Physical grounding brings the user back to their body and the present moment
Mechanics:
Large circle appears, expanding and contracting
Text inside circle: "Breathe In" (4s) → "Breathe Out" (4s)
User must press and hold a designated area
Must maintain hold for 3 full breath cycles (24 seconds total)
If user releases early, progress resets to 0
Upon completion, user proceeds to success screen
The Hold Mechanic:
User places thumb on "Hold" area
Must maintain contact for 24 seconds
If they let go, timer resets
This prevents "rage quitting" the app
Physical commitment reinforces mental commitment
